sudo  service docker  start

docker version
docker info


### Previous syntax of commands
docker run
### New syntax 
docker container run


    Start a container 
    sudo docker container run -d  -p 80:8080 --name nginx  nginx
    -p is for port mapping from a docker network port to a host port
    -name is the name you want to give to your container
    -d is for running in detach mode (if you start without detach the container will stop when you exit)

    Stop a container 

    Start a container

    Remove a container

    List running containers

    List all containers (and the stopped ones)